@robconery This is a tongue-in-cheek woaaah! Slow down there! (although the last comment you just wrote whilst I was writing this is waaaay more along the lines of what I'm thinking).

I'm starting this conversation so we can gather together concrete ideas on how to move forward **because** the task is big and scary for someone on their own. I strongly believe if we collaborate as a group of smart people, we can come up with a game plan, and a set of steps to get us there. No need for a big freeze or scary rewrite.

@hswolff did some excellent work last year to start moving the ship in the right direction. I think if there's a group of us all working on a plan we'll get there much less painfully.

All that said, let me comment on a couple of things:

@JoshWillik (and @gleneivey) The reason #827 is still open is because there are competing ideas, and it's very difficult to assess which direction is the right one. As you say - there are great ideas in both PRs, but there's also my underlying niggling feeling that the reason it's been so hard to get a sensible solution is due to underlying problems (that are what this discussion is intended to get to the bottom of).

