Putting an email address in a query parameter field hits the host of the email address. To fix this I had to encode the components. I put my hack at the start of parseUri, but it should probably go somewhere else.
```javascript
function parseUri (str) {
  str = str.replace(/\?(.*)/gi, function($0, $1) {
    var parts = $1.split('='),
      hasQuestion = $0.indexOf('?') === 0,
      encoded = encodeURIComponent(parts[0]) + '=' + encodeURIComponent(parts[1]);

    if (hasQuestion) {
      encoded = '?' + encoded;
    }
    return encoded;
  });
```

